In such matters, you should be ahead of the way, because if the problem overtakes you, then only emergency measures remain.
And now we are in this situation.
Even the interim government that replaced SYRIZA did more in just seven days than Mr. Tsipras did in seven months.
I am sure that these actions of the interim government, which is provided with valuable assistance, the President of the Republic, who called on the EU summit, will allow to find a solution.
We need to see how many refugees will be able to leave the country, and note that refugees are not illegal immigrants.
These are victims of the war in Syria, the victims of some extraordinary events that have occurred with them.
This issue has a deeply humanitarian aspect, and we will adhere to the position that European politicians must adopt in this new situation.
The corresponding decision should be made at the EU summit, the United Nations should also be involved.
We also need better coordination, more effective border control and reception centres.
We must also effectively use the economic assistance we receive from the EU in order to be able to cope with this pressing issue.
Euronews: Mr. Maymarakis, thank you for the interview.
Vangelis Meimarakis: Thank you.
