The humiliation of trances on the part of cellmates is guaranteed, - says Vladislav Grib.
Depending on how large a city, how many criminals with an indefinite sex, you need to calculate where to distribute them.
Separate pre-trial detention is definitely not needed - only cameras, blocks in prisons.
Yes, a separate colony is possible if there are many transgender people.
As Gryb explained, the block can contain 50 or 100 people, and if a specialized corps is created in Russia alone, then transgender prisoners will be able to go to serve sentences there from any regions.
Citizens are detained in a pre-trial detention center at the place of commission of the crime, so the receipt of transvestites or transgender people from other subjects during the investigation and trial are unrealistic, but to introduce such a practice for already convicts in a separate colony - yes, "Mushroom believes.
