At the same time, the international expert on reproductive health on the territory of the Russian Federation Boris Lordkipanidze noted that the introduction of a new system of distribution of transgender criminals in the colony can strongly postpone the beginning of serving the sentence of convicts.
A commission is created - it is a matter of sexology, psychiatrists conduct long-term observations, this is not one test, on the basis of which a high-precision conclusion is made.
Today’s psychiatry capabilities allow this.
Therefore, before changing the floor, potential patients always undergo such examinations - they accurately show whether the sex change with surgery is the necessary measure, - says Lordkipanidze.
However, it is difficult for me to imagine how to introduce this system to the convicts, because on average it takes a month for such a survey.
The doctor, despite the fact that in general the idea of creating separate blocks for transsexuals supported, also doubts that in the current economic conditions it will be advisable to allocate funds for the construction of new premises, medical examinations - transgender people in Russia.
It is difficult to calculate, there are no official statistics, but if we take into account that there are about 5% homosexuals in Russia, then we can say that there are even fewer transgender people, and those who have such a deviation and also commit crimes are a small number at all.
