This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers "Top-1000 Russian Managers" is published for the 16th time.
Being a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian managers of the highest echelon, the study summarizes the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of the rating of the last year.
Last year’s winners are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate of the rating of the current year and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates included in the original list is offered to nominate up to ten new managers from other companies, which it would be advisable to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following managers of the functional areas of the company: CFO, Commercial Director, Marketing Director, Director of HR, IT Director, Director of Public and Corporate Relations, Director of Relations with Authorities, Director of Corporate Governance.
Each expert-proposed manager is sent an invitation to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate his management team and up to ten new executives from other companies.
The nomination of candidates on an industry principle is carried out on the basis of the industry classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, forestry and timber industry, mechanical engineering, media business, metallurgy, multidisciplinary holdings, professional services, communications and telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel.
Each participant is provided with a login and password to log in to www.top1000.amr.ru, where they see information about the remaining participants and can make their ratings on the criteria offered for each functional direction.
The basis of the rating construction methodology is the principle of "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
This principle allows you to get the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at meetings of expert commissions.
All interested candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of previous years are invited to face-to-face meetings of the expert commissions.
The commissions are organized on a functional basis: a commission for the approval of the list of senior leaders and eight commissions for the approval of heads of functional areas.
At meetings of expert commissions, it is proposed to approve the submitted lists in alphabetical order (places are stored strictly according to the Internet assessment and are classified information before the publication of the rating) or make updating their adjustments according to the attached list of reserve candidates.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Kommersant".
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
The comfortable rate for an investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the market for lending to small and medium-sized businesses in January-April of this year fell by 40%.
What do you think the situation is today?
After the panic of the end of 2014 - early 2015, the volume of lending to SMEs decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Lending at 25-30% per annum was not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could put in an increased rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-returns, now it is impossible to do this: bets are already sky-high.
For business, the current level of interest rates on SME loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their payback.
The level of rates of 10-13% would allow businesses to invest in a wide range of projects and form an attractive profitability on them.
How much do you assess the demand of entrepreneurs for loans are satisfied with?
After the CB drop in the interest rate, the situation has improved slightly.
Credit resources have become more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, business does not understand the prospects for its development and future income.
Today, business has one way out: you need to learn how to work, focusing on today's economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, control the movement of funds.
At the same time, in the presence of financial resources, it is worth using new technologies that allow you to modernize equipment, reduce production costs and energy supply.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends of the SME lending market will strengthen and will influence its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for lowering the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator is demonstrating consistency in the issue of lowering the key rate.
However, a radical drop in the price of loans for SMEs should not be expected.
In the current situation, the problem, first of all, is inflation, which makes an increased interest rate necessary to generate real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even with the reduction of the rates of the Central Bank.
If we talk about the level of delay, then traditionally small and medium-sized businesses, limited both in the possibilities of replenishing funds and in the options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to creditors.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country’s economy.
