Yesterday, 12 mandates were distributed among political parties, depending on their votes.
On the lists of United Russia, six deputy seats in the city Duma rely on Dmitry Svatkovsky, Dmitry Krasnov, Vasily Shupranov, Elizaveta Solonchenko, Vyacheslav Rasteryaev and Igor Nagorny.
The only mandate of the LDPR was received by the leader of the party Vladimir Zhirinovsky.
Two mandates of the CPRF are distributed between Vladimir Bulanov and State Duma deputy Alexander Tarnaev.
Three mandates of “Fair Russia” go to Alexander Razumovsky, Igor Bogdanov and Mikhail Shalyugin.
Now, within five days, these candidates must decide whether they will work as deputies in the city Duma: in case of refusal of the mandate, he will move to the next candidate on the party list.
Chairman of the city election Commission Alexander Makeev told the members of the Commission that he was on duty for “sending telegrams to Zhirinovsky and others” for the refusal of mandates.
